Title: Pupils praise 'maths whisperer' teacher after entire class achieves A* in GCSE
Description:
A school in Cardiff is celebrating after an entire class achieved A* in their maths GCSE, after sitting the exam six months early. 

The Year 11 group at Fitzalan High School now refer to teacher Francis Elive as "the maths whisperer" as some of the class even came close to achieving full marks

Title: How to write a simple operating system in assembly language
Description:
This document shows you how to write and build your first operating system
in x86 assembly language. It explains what you need, the fundamentals of the PC boot process and
assembly language, and how to take it further. The resulting OS will be very small (fitting into
a bootloader) and have very few features, but it's a starting point for you to explore further.
